{
  "texts": [
    "This ability to retain and potentially reveal personal information calls for robust measures to ensure data privacy and prevent unauthorized access.",
    "The use of LLMs in healthcare (25, 26) has also raised privacy and security concerns, particularly regarding sensitive medical information (39, 40).",
    "Clinical notes, encompassing physician consultations, nursing assessments, lab results, and more, are often stored in free-text formats that may include identifiable or confidential patient information.",
    "Unauthorized access to this information poses significant risks to patient confidentiality and privacy.",
    "Regulations such as the U.S. Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA) mandate the removal of re-identifying information from medical records before dissemination to preserve patient confidentiality (41, 42)."
  ]
}